==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/twɪŋk/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪŋk|-ɪŋk]]

===Etymology 1===
Cognate with Middle High German [[zwinken]] (German [[zwinkern]]).

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# To [[twinkle]], [[sparkle]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# A [[twinkle]]; a [[glint]].

===Etymology 2===
Imitative.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# The [[chaffinch]].

===Etymology 3===
From [[twinkie]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# (''gay slang'') A young, attractive, slim man, usually having little body hair.
# (''derogatory slang'') A weak or effeminate man, whether gay or not.

=====Synonyms=====
*(''gay slang: young, attractive, slim man''): [[chicken]]
*(''weak or effeminate man''): [[poof]] (''British''), [[fag]] (''especially US''), [[faggot]] (''especially US'')

